# Naming Conventions

## Custom Elements (Web Components)

- All custom element tag names MUST be prefixed with `n-`
- Examples: `<n-app>`, `<n-button>`, `<n-modal>`

## Custom Attributes

- All custom attributes MUST be prefixed with `n-`
- Examples: `n-href`, `n-if`, `n-for`, `n-bind`

## JavaScript/TypeScript Classes

- All framework classes MUST be prefixed with `NativeJs`
- Examples: `NativeJsComponent`, `NativeJsRouter`, `NativeJsApp`

## Examples

```html
<!-- Custom element with custom attribute -->
<n-button n-click="handleClick">Click me</n-button>

<!-- Router link -->
<a n-href="/about">About</a>
```

```typescript
// Component class
class NativeJsComponent extends HTMLElement {
  // ...
}

// Custom component extending base
class MyComponent extends NativeJsComponent {
  // ...
}
```
